-DON'T WORRY ABOUT NEELY, PAL.

15:59.045 --> 16:00.524
SHE'S ONE OF THE BEST
LIFEGUARDS WE HAVE.

16:00.655 --> 16:02.048
-OKAY, IF YOU'RE NOT
WORRIED, I'M NOT WORRIED.

16:02.178 --> 16:03.788
-HEY.
-MITCH: HEY.

16:03.919 --> 16:05.790
-GUESS WHAT? I HAVE AN
INTERVIEW WITH CALVIN KLEIN.

16:05.921 --> 16:07.618
-WAY TO GO. I HAVE TO CHANGE

16:07.749 --> 16:10.404
-GREAT, IS THIS THE
INTERNSHIP YOU TOLD ME ABOUT?

16:10.534 --> 16:12.319
-ACTUALLY, IT'S
A REAL JOB OFFER.

16:12.449 --> 16:13.929
I SENT SOME OF THE SAMPLES I
DID FOR CALIFORNIA LIFESTYLES.

16:14.060 --> 16:15.975
I DIDN'T EXPECT A RESPONSE.

16:16.105 --> 16:17.672
-WHEN'S THE INTERVIEW?

16:17.802 --> 16:19.717
-TOMORROW. I FLY TO NEW
YORK AT 5:30 IN THE MORNING.

16:19.848 --> 16:22.198
-HEY. DID I HEAR YOU SAY
YOU'RE GOING TO NEW YORK?

16:22.329 --> 16:24.374
-OH, THAT'S RIGHT. YOU'RE
GOING TO SEE LANI, HUH?

16:24.505 --> 16:25.680
-YEAH, I'M ON THE EARLY
BIRD TOMORROW MORNING.

16:25.810 --> 16:27.029
-ME, TOO.

16:27.160 --> 16:28.030
-EXCELLENT, YOU
CAN CARRY MY BAGS.

16:28.161 --> 16:29.553
-[LAUGHING SARCASTICALLY]

16:29.684 --> 16:31.207
-OFF TO OPEN THE TOWER.
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

16:31.338 --> 16:34.036
-IN THE MEANTIME, I
NEED TO TX WITH SOMEONE.

16:34.167 --> 16:35.168
WHO WOULD WANT TO
TAKE MY SCHEDULE

16:35.298 --> 16:36.430
FOR THE NEXT FEW DAYS?

16:36.560 --> 16:37.997
-DON'T LOOK AT ME.

16:38.910 --> 16:40.042
-HOW ABOUT NEELY?

16:40.564 --> 16:42.566
-NEELY'S BACK? SINCE WHEN?

16:42.697 --> 16:43.524
-THIS MORNING.

16:44.960 --> 16:45.787
-WHAT TOWER?

16:45.917 --> 16:51.053
-[PLANE ROARING]

16:53.490 --> 16:55.231
-YEAH, THE NEW REGULATORS
THAT DACOR HAVE

16:55.362 --> 16:56.406
ARE UNBELIEVABLE.
-[PHONE RINGING]

16:56.537 --> 16:57.799
-EXCUSE ME.

16:57.929 --> 16:59.540
BUCHANNON.

16:59.670 --> 17:01.803
-MITCH? DID YOU DO THE
TOWER ASSIGNING THIS MORNING?

17:02.499 --> 17:04.022
-NEELY, YOU HAVE TO SPEAK UP,

17:04.153 --> 17:05.328
I CAN'T HEAR YOU.
-CRAIG: PUT HER ON SPEAKER.

17:05.459 --> 17:06.938
-OF COURSE YOU CAN'T HEAR ME.

17:07.069 --> 17:10.377
THERE'S 747S TAKING
OFF DIRECT OVERHEAD.

17:10.507 --> 17:11.682
-YOU PUT HER AT KILGORE 1?

17:11.813 --> 17:13.423
-I DIDN'T.

17:13.554 --> 17:15.425
-I DIDN'T WANT ANYONE TO
ACCUSE YOU OF PLAYING FAVORITES.

17:15.556 --> 17:18.124
-YEAH, NO SPECIAL TREATMENT
FOR THE BOSS'S WIFE.

17:18.253 --> 17:19.473
-WELCOME BACK, NEELY.

17:19.603 --> 17:20.517
-WHAT DID SHE SAY?

17:20.647 --> 17:22.040
-ALL: WELCOME BACK.

17:22.171 --> 17:24.391
-OH, THANKS, GUYS.
IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK.

17:24.521 --> 17:26.696
ALTHOUGH, I THINK
I'LL NEVER HEAR AGAIN.

17:26.828 --> 17:28.569
-[PLANES ROARING]

17:28.699 --> 17:29.874
-THE TOWER IS SHAKING.

17:30.658 --> 17:31.702
-[LAUGHING]

17:31.833 --> 17:32.616
-NEELY: CRAIG?

17:32.747 --> 17:33.878
-YES, NEELY.

17:34.009 --> 17:35.576
I'M GOING TO GET
YOU FOR THIS.

17:36.272 --> 17:37.317
-OKAY.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.854
-[BABY CRYING]

17:52.984 --> 17:55.074
-OH, HEY, HEY, HEY.

17:56.423 --> 17:57.728
I GOT YOU, HONEY.

17:57.859 --> 17:59.469
-SHE'S ALL YOURS.

17:59.600 --> 18:01.558
NEELY'S MOM IS GONNA PICK
HER UP IN ABOUT AN HOUR.

18:01.689 --> 18:02.820
-OH, HERE YOU GO.

18:02.951 --> 18:04.822
-EXCUSE ME, SORRY
TO BOTHER YOU.

18:04.953 --> 18:06.259
I KNOW SOMEONE WHO
USED TO WORK HERE.

18:06.389 --> 18:08.522
NEELY CAPSHAW? IS
SHE STILL AROUND?

18:11.002 --> 18:13.222
IF NOT, DO YOU KNOW WHERE I
MIGHT BE ABLE TO FIND HER?

18:13.353 --> 18:14.658
-AND YOU ARE?
-PETER: PETER ANDREWS.

18:14.789 --> 18:15.746
-HER EX-HUSBAND?

18:15.877 --> 18:17.226
-YES.

18:17.357 --> 18:18.749
-OH, DID YOU COME
BY TO SEE ASHLEY?

18:19.576 --> 18:20.490
-PETER: I BEG YOUR PARDON?

18:21.230 --> 18:22.536
-DOES NEELY KNOW
YOU'RE IN TOWN?

18:22.666 --> 18:24.190
-NOT UNLESS SHE'S PSYCHIC.

18:24.320 --> 18:25.887
I'VE BEEN IN THE HIMALAYAS
THE LAST SIX MONTHS

18:26.017 --> 18:27.323
AND I'M AFRAID
WE LOST TOUCH.

18:28.455 --> 18:31.066
-WELL, THAT'S FUNNY, SHE
SAID SHE SAW YOU IN ALASKA.

18:31.197 --> 18:32.285
-ALASKA?

18:32.415 --> 18:33.982
-YEAH, LAST MONTH IN JUNO.

18:34.113 --> 18:36.811
WITH YOUR NEW WIFE
AND NEW BABY.

18:36.941 --> 18:39.379
-THAT SEEMS RATHER ODD
SINCE I'M NOT MARRIED.

18:39.509 --> 18:40.858
I CERTAINLY DON'T
HAVE A CHILD.

18:44.210 --> 18:45.341
-YEAH, YOU DO.

18:46.212 --> 18:49.128
PETER, THIS IS YOUR
DAUGHTER, ASHLEY.

18:50.216 --> 18:54.655
-[CALMING MUSIC]

19:08.016 --> 19:10.018
-HEY, PAL. YOU OKAY?

19:12.455 --> 19:13.761
-GO AHEAD, SAY IT.

19:13.891 --> 19:15.676
-SAY WHAT?

19:15.806 --> 19:18.461
-WHAT'D YOU BEEN THINKING
SINCE I CAME BACK FROM ALASKA.

19:18.592 --> 19:21.247
THAT I GOT CAUGHT UP IN
SOME SHIP BOARD ROMANCE

19:21.377 --> 19:23.162
AND TEMPORARILY
LOST MY MIND.

19:24.380 --> 19:26.034
-THAT'S NOT WHAT I THINK.

19:27.557 --> 19:30.430
I THINK YOU REALLY LOVE NEELY
AND THAT'S WHY IT HURTS.

19:31.909 --> 19:33.694
I ALSO THINK THAT'S
WHY SHE DESERVES

19:33.824 --> 19:35.348
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT.

19:35.478 --> 19:37.176
THE FACT IS YOU DON'T KNOW
WHO'S TELLING THE TRUTH.

19:38.786 --> 19:41.180
YOU SHOULD AT LEAST HEAR
HER SIDE OF THE STORY.

19:43.051 --> 19:46.054
-PLAYED THIS THING OVER IN
MY MIND A THOUSAND TIMES.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.492
SHE HAD THE WHOLE
THING PLANNED.

19:51.668 --> 19:53.975
-WHY WOULD SHE LIE ABOUT
SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

19:54.105 --> 19:57.500
-YOU READ HER FILE. SHE'S
BEEN LYING HER WHOLE LIFE.

19:57.631 --> 19:58.849
-[CAR HONKING]

19:58.980 --> 20:01.765
-HEY, MITCH. I
JUST SAW NEELY.

20:01.896 --> 20:03.724
SHE'S GONNA WORK
OUT AFTER HER SHIFT.

20:03.854 --> 20:04.942
SAYS SHE'LL SEE YOU AT HOME.

20:05.073 --> 20:06.205
-THANKS.

20:06.814 --> 20:07.989
-IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

20:08.119 --> 20:09.643
-YEAH, IT'S JUST FINE, J.D.

20:11.166 --> 20:13.342
-NEVER HAD A BETTER DAY.

20:15.344 --> 20:20.349
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

20:24.440 --> 20:25.833
MITCH: WHAT HAPPENED
WITH PETER?

20:25.963 --> 20:27.704
-NEELY: PETER'S MARRIED.

20:27.835 --> 20:29.271
-MITCH: WHAT?

20:29.402 --> 20:32.622
-YEAH, I MET HIS WIFE
AND HIS LITTLE BABY BOY.

20:33.884 --> 20:35.146
-YOU'RE KIDDING.

20:36.104 --> 20:38.237
-OBVIOUSLY WE'RE NOT
GETTING BACK TOGETHER.

20:39.107 --> 20:42.023
HE'LL COME AND SEE
ASHLEY WHENEVER HE CAN,

20:42.153 --> 20:44.634
BUT OTHERWISE
WE'RE ON OUR OWN.

20:45.418 --> 20:46.810
-ARE YOU OKAY WITH THAT?

20:46.941 --> 20:49.378
-WELL, TO BE HONEST WITH
YOU, IT'S A HUGE RELIEF.

20:49.509 --> 20:51.075
I KNEW IN MY HEART
IT WOULD NEVER WORK.

20:51.206 --> 20:53.469
I MEAN, HOW CAN
YOU BE WITH SOMEONE

20:53.600 --> 20:55.254
WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE
WITH SOMEONE ELSE?

20:57.517 --> 21:01.434
ONLY QUESTION NOW
IS DOES HE LOVE ME?

21:04.219 --> 21:06.134
-WHO'S HE?

21:07.614 --> 21:08.702
-YOU.

21:11.748 --> 21:12.575
-ME?

21:13.968 --> 21:16.100
-DO YOU?
-MITCH: DO I WHAT?

21:16.231 --> 21:18.146
-LOVE ME.

21:23.369 --> 21:27.982
-NEELY, I LOVE YOU MORE
THAN ANYONE I'VE EVER LOVED

21:28.112 --> 21:29.288
IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

21:38.688 --> 21:40.821
-SURPRISE. STILL HERE?

21:40.951 --> 21:41.822
-YEAH.

21:43.214 --> 21:44.433
-MITCH, WHAT'S WRONG?

21:45.608 --> 21:48.089
-SOMEONE CAME BY
TO SEE YOU TODAY.

21:49.612 --> 21:50.613
-WHO?

21:53.007 --> 21:54.487
-MITCH: YOUR EX-HUSBAND.

21:54.617 --> 21:55.444
-PETER?

21:55.575 --> 21:57.185
-INTERESTING THOUGHT.

21:57.316 --> 21:59.579
CLAIMS HE'S BEEN IN THE
HIMALAYAS THE LAST SIX MONTHS.

21:59.709 --> 22:02.973
THAT HE'S NEVER BEEN TO ALASKA
AND THAT HE HASN'T SEEN YOU

22:03.104 --> 22:04.932
IN OVER A YEAR.

22:05.062 --> 22:07.064
-WHAT, MITCH? THIS IS ANOTHER
ONE OF YOUR PRACTICAL JOKES.

22:07.195 --> 22:09.806
-HAD ABSOLUTELY NO IDEA
THAT HE WAS A FATHER.

22:11.199 --> 22:13.157
-OH, MY GOD. YOU DIDN'T
LET HIM NEAR ASHLEY.

22:13.288 --> 22:15.682
HE PROBABLY CAME
HERE TO KIDNAP HER.

22:15.812 --> 22:17.118
WHERE IS SHE?
WHERE'S MY BABY?

22:17.248 --> 22:18.424
-YOUR MOTHER CAME
BY TO PICK HER UP.

22:18.554 --> 22:19.729
-LOOK, I WANNA
CALL AND MAKE SURE.

22:19.860 --> 22:21.296
-WHY DID YOU LIE
TO ME ON THE CRUISE?

22:21.427 --> 22:22.993
WHY DID YOU TELL ME
YOU WENT TO SEE PETER

22:23.124 --> 22:24.691
AND THAT HE WAS MARRIED?
WHY DID YOU DO THAT? WHY?

22:24.821 --> 22:26.736
-LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON HERE, MITCH,

22:26.867 --> 22:28.782
BUT MY ONLY CONCERN AT
THE MOMENT IS THE SAFETY

22:28.912 --> 22:30.523
OF MY CHILD, NOW
PLEASE LET ME GO.

22:30.653 --> 22:32.089
-NOT UNTIL YOU
ANSWER MY QUESTION!

22:32.220 --> 22:33.830
WHY DID YOU LIE TO ME? WHY?

22:33.961 --> 22:36.137
-BECAUSE I DIDN'T
THINK IT WOULD MATTER!

22:36.267 --> 22:40.533
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT YOU WERE
GOING TO PROPOSE TO ME.

22:40.663 --> 22:43.318
ALL I WAS THINKING WAS
THAT I DIDN'T WANT TO DEAL

22:43.449 --> 22:44.232
WITH MY EX-HUSBAND.

22:44.363 --> 22:45.929
-OH, COME ON.

22:46.060 --> 22:47.583
YOU COULD'VE SAID SOMETHING
TO ME AFTER I PROPOSED.

22:47.714 --> 22:50.238
-I KNOW, I KNOW.
I SHOULD HAVE.

22:51.457 --> 22:52.806
I WAS STUPID.

22:52.936 --> 22:55.025
-OH, THAT'S NOT IT.
YOU'RE NOT STUPID.

22:56.723 --> 23:00.640
-I WAS ALSO IN LOVE. I
FELT LIKE I WAS IN A DREAM.

23:00.770 --> 23:03.773
I DIDN'T WANT TO WAKE UP.
I DIDN'T WANT IT TO END.

23:07.690 --> 23:11.433
IF I HAD TOLD YOU THE TRUTH,
WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE DONE?

23:12.347 --> 23:15.350
-YOU DON'T LIE TO
SOMEONE THAT YOU LOVE.

23:15.481 --> 23:17.483
-I DIDN'T WANT TO LOSE
YOU. I STILL DON'T.

23:17.613 --> 23:19.136
MITCH, PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

23:19.267 --> 23:20.790
DON'T LET PETER
COME BETWEEN US.

23:20.921 --> 23:23.445
-IT'S NOT ABOUT PETER.
IT'S ABOUT YOU.

23:23.576 --> 23:25.142
-WE CAN WORK THIS OUT.

23:25.273 --> 23:27.406
-NOT IF I CAN'T BELIEVE
ANOTHER WORD YOU SAY.

23:28.276 --> 23:32.106
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

23:32.236 --> 23:35.979
-IF THAT'S THE WAY YOU FEEL,
THEN I WON'T SAY ANOTHER WORD.

23:48.557 --> 23:51.865
-[PHONE RINGING]

23:51.995 --> 23:52.866
-HELLO?

23:52.996 --> 23:54.911
-HEY, HOW'D IT GO?

23:55.042 --> 23:57.087
-MITCH: I CAN'T
TALK RIGHT NOW, PAL.

23:57.784 --> 23:59.133
-IS SHE RIGHT THERE?

23:59.263 --> 24:01.483
-NO, NO. SHE'S UPSTAIRS
LOCKED IN THE BEDROOM.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.398
I'M DOWNSTAIRS
MAKING UP THE COUCH.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.748
-WELL, THAT PRETTY MUCH
GIVES ME THE PICTURE.

24:07.141 --> 24:09.317
-I JUST DON'T KNOW HOW I'M
GOING TO TRUST HER AFTER THIS.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.014
-YEAH, THE QUESTION
BECOMES WHAT ARE YOU GOING

24:11.145 --> 24:12.538
TO DO ABOUT IT?

24:12.668 --> 24:14.627
-I KNOW. I DON'T WANT
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

24:15.715 --> 24:17.586
LISTEN, I'M ABOUT TO DROP.

24:17.717 --> 24:19.153
-CRAIG: GET SOME SLEEP.

24:19.283 --> 24:20.676
I'LL CHECK ON YOU FIRST
THING IN THE MORNING.

24:20.807 --> 24:23.374
-OKAY, THANKS. HEY,
THANKS FOR CALLING.

24:23.505 --> 24:24.375
-YEAH.

24:26.595 --> 24:31.948
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

24:39.347 --> 24:40.609
-MITCH: OW!
-[GLASS SHATTERING]

24:40.740 --> 24:41.610
-MITCH: WHAT A DAY.

24:43.133 --> 24:48.356
-[THRILLING MUSIC]

24:53.622 --> 24:55.145
-WELCOME ABOARD.
-APRIL: HI.

24:55.276 --> 24:56.712
-FIRST CLASS IS TO YOUR
RIGHT. ENJOY YOUR FLIGHT.

24:56.843 --> 24:58.061
-THANK YOU.

24:58.192 --> 24:59.367
-EXCUSE ME.
-OH, WE'RE TOGETHER.

24:59.498 --> 25:01.282
-I STILL NEED TO
SEE YOUR TICKET.

25:02.631 --> 25:03.502
-OKAY.

25:05.242 --> 25:06.592
-I'M AFRAID THAT
YOUR SEAT IS IN COACH.

25:07.375 --> 25:09.377
-WHAT? HOW CAN THAT BE?

25:10.378 --> 25:12.119
OH, THEY MUST'VE GIVEN
ME THE WRONG TICKET.

25:12.249 --> 25:13.686
-CODY.

25:13.816 --> 25:14.730
-AND I SUPPOSE YOU'RE
ON YOUR HONEYMOON?

25:14.861 --> 25:16.689
-HOW'D YOU GUESS?

25:16.819 --> 25:18.081
-I DON'T KNOW HIM.

25:19.082 --> 25:20.127
-COME ON, BUDDY. LET'S GO.

25:21.998 --> 25:23.391
-APRIL.

25:25.175 --> 25:27.656
I DON'T SUPPOSE THERE'S
ANY WAY YOU CAN UPGRADE ME.

25:27.787 --> 25:30.441
LOOKED LIKE A LOT OF
EMPTY SEATS UP THERE.

25:30.572 --> 25:32.792
-NOT AFTER THAT
LAME PERFORMANCE.

25:32.922 --> 25:35.272
BESIDES, I COULD
USE A GUY LIKE YOU.

25:35.403 --> 25:36.796
-REALLY?

25:36.926 --> 25:39.407
-THAT IS IF YOU'RE
REALLY A LIFEGUARD.

25:39.538 --> 25:40.930
-YEAH, I'M A LIFEGUARD.

25:42.192 --> 25:43.411
-HERE'S YOUR SEAT.

25:45.021 --> 25:46.545
-THOUGHT I WAS IN 17A.

25:46.675 --> 25:49.199
-YOU WERE, BUT TYLER HERE
IS TRAVELING BY HIMSELF

25:49.330 --> 25:50.853
AND HE COULD
USE THE COMPANY.

25:51.811 --> 25:53.769
-AND MY INCENTIVE WOULD BE?

25:54.814 --> 25:56.163
-FREE HEADPHONES.

25:59.340 --> 26:00.428
-GREAT.

26:08.479 --> 26:10.612
HOW YOU DOING, PAL?
MY NAME'S CODY.

26:10.743 --> 26:11.613
-I'M TYLER.

26:12.222 --> 26:14.181
-NICE TO MEET YOU, TYLER.

26:14.311 --> 26:16.792
-THEY'RE SERVING SAUSAGE
AND PANCAKES FOR BREAKFAST.

26:17.445 --> 26:18.925
-REALLY?

26:19.055 --> 26:21.101
-LAST TIME I FLEW, I
HAD A CHICKEN POT PIE.

26:21.231 --> 26:23.799
-OH, YEAH? HOW WAS IT?

26:23.930 --> 26:25.627
-MADE ME BARF.

26:28.674 --> 26:29.979
-OKAY.

26:33.548 --> 26:34.462
-SAY WHEN.

26:34.593 --> 26:36.551
-THAT'S GREAT. THANKS.

26:36.682 --> 26:37.900
-WE'LL HAVE FULL
COCKTAIL SERVICE ONCE
WE'RE UP IN THE AIR.

26:38.031 --> 26:39.032
-OKAY.

26:44.428 --> 26:45.212
HI.

26:45.342 --> 26:46.561
-GOOD MORNING.

26:46.692 --> 26:50.043
-WOW, I'M A BIG
FAN OF YOUR FILMS.

26:50.173 --> 26:51.697
-OH, THANK YOU.
THAT'S SWEET OF YOU.

26:51.827 --> 26:53.524
-ESPECIALLY THE OBLITERATOR.

26:53.655 --> 26:57.224
YOU KNOW THAT ACTION SEQUENCE
AT THE END IS AWESOME.

26:57.354 --> 26:58.399
I'M APRIL GIMINSKI.

26:58.529 --> 27:00.488
-HANS.
-APRIL: HI.

27:00.619 --> 27:02.403
-OH, EXCUSE ME, SORRY.

27:03.404 --> 27:07.626
I'M SORRY, I BELIEVE I
HAVE 7A IN THE WINDOW.

27:09.236 --> 27:10.933
-ACTUALLY, WOULD YOU BE MORE
COMFORTABLE ON THE AISLE?

27:11.064 --> 27:12.543
-WOULD YOU MIND?
-NOT AT ALL.

27:12.674 --> 27:13.806
-GREAT.

27:13.936 --> 27:15.155
-HERE, LET ME HELP YOU.
-THANKS.

27:15.285 --> 27:16.678
-PILOT: GOOD
MORNING, EVERYBODY.

27:16.809 --> 27:18.506
ON BEHALF OF COAST WEST
AIRLINES FLIGHT 619

27:18.637 --> 27:20.029
TO NEW YORK'S JOHN
F. KENNEDY AIRPORT,

27:20.160 --> 27:21.683
I'D LIKE TO WELCOME
YOU ABOARD.

27:21.814 --> 27:23.424
MY NAME'S BRENT MUELLER,
YOUR CAPTAIN THIS MORNING.

27:23.554 --> 27:25.818
TIME EN ROUTE, FIVE
HOURS, 15 MINUTES.

27:25.948 --> 27:28.472
WE'LL BE CRUISING
AT 37,000 FEET.

27:28.603 --> 27:30.866
WE'VE GOT SOME THUNDER
STORMS REPORTED EN ROUTE.

27:30.997 --> 27:32.825
COURTESY OF EL NINO.

27:32.955 --> 27:35.958
IN FACT, JUST OFF SHORE, WE'VE
GOT SOME DEVELOPING ACTIVITY.

27:36.089 --> 27:38.091
WHAT THAT MEANS IS WE
COULD HAVE A BUMP OR TWO

27:38.221 --> 27:40.180
AFTER TAKE OFF, SO
PLEASE STAY IN YOUR SEATS

27:40.310 --> 27:42.486
WITH YOUR SEAT BELTS
FASTENED, THANK YOU.

27:45.620 --> 27:47.709
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO IN
NEW YORK? YOU LIVE THERE?

27:47.840 --> 27:50.625
-NO, WE'RE GOING TO
VISIT MY GRANDPARENTS.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.192
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

27:52.322 --> 27:53.541
-GONNA SEE MY GIRLFRIEND.

27:53.672 --> 27:54.847
-SHE LIVE IN NEW YORK?

27:54.977 --> 27:56.500
-YUP, SHE JUST MOVED THERE.

27:56.631 --> 27:58.372
SHE OPENS TOMORROW
ON BROADWAY.

27:58.502 --> 27:59.939
SHE'S A DANCER.

28:01.331 --> 28:02.768
-ARE YOU A DANCER?

28:02.898 --> 28:06.554
-[LAUGHS] NO, I
AM NOT A DANCER.

28:13.474 --> 28:15.084
-SO, WHEN ARE YOU DUE?

28:15.215 --> 28:16.607
-NOT FOR ANOTHER MONTH.

28:18.740 --> 28:20.350
I KNOW I'M HUGE.

28:20.481 --> 28:22.396
-NO, YOU'RE NOT.

28:22.526 --> 28:24.528
-IT'S OKAY, WE'RE GONNA
NEED THAT MUCH TIME

28:24.659 --> 28:25.704
TO COME UP WITH A NAME.

28:25.834 --> 28:27.401
-IS IT A BOY OR A GIRL?

28:27.531 --> 28:29.708
-WE DON'T KNOW YET,
SO WE'VE GOT TO COME UP

28:29.838 --> 28:31.492
WITH TWO SETS OF NAMES.

28:32.058 --> 28:34.974
I LIKE SHARON OR
SHEILA IF IT'S A GIRL

28:35.104 --> 28:38.194
AND ROGER OR ROBERT
IF IT'S A BOY.

28:38.325 --> 28:41.023
MY HUSBAND LIKES
HECTOR IF IT'S A BOY

28:41.154 --> 28:43.286
AND SYDNEY IF IT'S A GIRL.

28:44.374 --> 28:46.768
YOU CAN SEE WHY WE'RE NOT
SPEAKING AT THE MOMENT.

28:46.899 --> 28:48.552
-ALL SET?
-ALL SET.

28:48.683 --> 28:50.511
-CLEAR RIGHT.
-CLEAR RIGHT.

28:50.641 --> 28:52.861
-TRAFFIC CONTROL: CENTER FIELD
WIND AT 25 GUSTING TO 30 SOUTH

28:52.992 --> 28:54.341
FIELD WIND AT 10.

28:54.471 --> 28:56.647
LAST AIRCRAFT REPORTED
LOSS OF 10 TO 15 KNOTS.

28:58.040 --> 29:00.260
COAST WEST 619, YOU
ARE CLEAR FOR TAKE OFF.

29:00.390 --> 29:02.044
-TOM, I'M JUST GONNA
CARRY A LITTLE EXTRA SPEED.

29:02.175 --> 29:04.264
WE'RE UPDATING A LITTLE SLOW.

29:04.394 --> 29:06.179
-OKAY. LET'S GO.

29:17.756 --> 29:19.148
-I HATE THIS PART.

29:19.279 --> 29:20.802
-IT'S GONNA BE OKAY, PAL.

29:28.070 --> 29:30.420
-WE MUST BE GOING
THROUGH THE STORM.

29:33.815 --> 29:37.210
-[THUNDER CRASHING]

29:37.340 --> 29:42.345
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

29:50.353 --> 29:52.355
-AIR SPEED. TIME
RATE'S DECREASING.

29:52.486 --> 29:53.313
-[BEEPING]

29:53.443 --> 29:55.315
-WIND SHEAR, WIND SHEAR.

30:00.842 --> 30:03.845
LIGHT BUZZ FIVE. 6500,
BUZZ LIGHT MINUS FIVE.

30:03.976 --> 30:06.500
SINK A THOUSAND,
MINUS 17, SINK 15.

30:06.630 --> 30:08.415
WE'RE LOSING IT.

30:08.545 --> 30:13.899
-[SCARED SHOUTING]

30:14.029 --> 30:16.466
-WHAT'S HAPPENING?
ARE WE GONNA CRASH?

30:19.339 --> 30:21.689
-[BEEPING]

30:31.003 --> 30:35.616
-[SCREAMING]

30:35.746 --> 30:36.965
-WE'RE NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

30:37.096 --> 30:38.401
TELL THE PASSENGERS
WE'RE GOING IN.

30:38.532 --> 30:39.925
-PREPARE FOR IMPACT.

30:40.055 --> 30:42.014
PREPARE FOR IMPACT.
PREPARE FOR IMPACT.

30:42.144 --> 30:43.493
-MY GOD.

30:43.624 --> 30:45.974
-HOLD YOUR HEAD BETWEEN
YOUR LEGS, TYLER.

30:47.236 --> 30:49.848
-MAYDAY,
MAYDAY, MAYDAY.

30:49.978 --> 30:53.416
-[SCREAMING]

31:15.699 --> 31:18.702
-PLEASE STAY CALM!
WE WILL GET YOU OUT.

31:20.704 --> 31:21.923
DON'T PANIC.

31:22.054 --> 31:27.233
-[SCREAMING AND SHOUTING]

31:29.278 --> 31:30.714
-TYLER, TYLER,
YOU ALL RIGHT?

31:30.845 --> 31:32.673
ALL RIGHT, COME ON, KID.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

31:32.803 --> 31:33.935
-CODY, HELP!

31:34.066 --> 31:35.241
-COME ON, COME
ON, COME ON!

31:36.242 --> 31:40.115
COME ON, STAY
WITH ME, TYLER.

31:52.606 --> 31:54.086
-APRIL: FRANCINE?

31:54.216 --> 31:55.043
FRANCINE?

31:56.305 --> 31:58.307
ARE YOU OKAY? ARE YOU OKAY?

31:58.829 --> 31:59.961
-I THINK SO.

32:00.092 --> 32:01.006
-OKAY, LET'S GET
THIS OFF YOU.

32:01.136 --> 32:02.311
-OKAY.
-APRIL: ANY PAIN?

32:02.442 --> 32:03.356
-NO.

32:03.486 --> 32:04.792
-OKAY, YOU ALL RIGHT?

32:04.923 --> 32:06.794
HANG IN THERE. HOLD ON.

32:07.621 --> 32:09.536
HANS! HANS?

32:10.189 --> 32:11.581
COME ON, YOU OKAY?

32:14.019 --> 32:15.324
YOU ALL RIGHT?

32:17.196 --> 32:18.327
-WHERE ARE WE?

32:19.850 --> 32:20.982
DO YOU SEE ANYTHING?

32:21.635 --> 32:23.463
-WE'RE STILL ABOVE WATER.

32:23.985 --> 32:25.944
I'M GONNA LOOK FOR
A WAY OUT, OKAY?

32:26.640 --> 32:28.859
OKAY? ALL RIGHT.

32:30.644 --> 32:35.954
-[SHOUTING]

32:36.084 --> 32:38.043
-OKAY, TYLER, WE GOTTA
PUT THIS ON YOU.

33:06.114 --> 33:08.029
OKAY, TYLER, IT'S
YOUR TURN, MAN.

33:08.160 --> 33:09.161
I'LL BE RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

33:09.291 --> 33:10.684
-I DON'T SEE ANYBODY ELSE.

33:11.467 --> 33:14.470
-WHAT ABOUT MY GLASSES?
I WON'T BE ABLE TO SEE.

33:14.601 --> 33:16.168
-I'LL HOLD YOUR
GLASSES, NOW GO.

33:16.298 --> 33:18.779
CLOSE YOUR EYES AND JUMP.

33:23.218 --> 33:25.699
TYLER! TYLER!

33:30.791 --> 33:32.880
TYLER! TYLER!

33:33.011 --> 33:34.229
-TYLER!

33:34.360 --> 33:35.491
-DO YOU SEE HIM?
-NO!

33:35.622 --> 33:37.102
-CODY: TYLER!
-WOMAN: TYLER!

33:37.232 --> 33:39.408
-DO YOU HEAR
MY VOICE? TYLER!

33:39.539 --> 33:41.149
TYLER!

33:44.196 --> 33:45.110
I CAN'T FIND HIM.

33:45.806 --> 33:48.200
-HE'LL TURN UP. I
NEED YOUR HELP HERE.

33:48.330 --> 33:50.463
-HE'S GOT A LIFE VEST ON,
HE COULDN'T HAVE DROWNED.

33:51.116 --> 33:51.942
TYLER!

33:52.073 --> 33:52.856
-CODY!

33:52.987 --> 33:53.770
-TYLER!

33:53.901 --> 33:54.858
-CODY!

34:01.952 --> 34:03.780
-[GROANING]

34:13.355 --> 34:14.574
-OH, MY GOD.

34:16.489 --> 34:17.880
WE'VE GOT TO GET THIS
OFF OF YOU. ARE YOU OKAY?

34:18.012 --> 34:19.143
-I THINK SO.

34:19.927 --> 34:22.016
-HANS, FRANCINE!
CAN YOU HELP?

34:24.366 --> 34:26.411
JUST HANG IN THERE,
JUST HANG IN THERE.

34:30.806 --> 34:32.157
WE GOTTA GET IT OFF.

34:34.376 --> 34:35.943
-WE NEED MORE HELP,
GO CHECK THE PILOTS.

34:36.639 --> 34:37.987
-I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

34:40.165 --> 34:41.382
-MAN: IT'S ON MY LEG.

34:43.297 --> 34:44.908
-[GRUNTING]

34:52.002 --> 34:55.702
-CAPTAIN? CAPTAIN?

34:55.831 --> 34:57.094
CAPTAIN?

34:57.225 --> 34:58.922
-IT ONLY OPENS
FROM THE INSIDE.

34:59.053 --> 35:00.533
THEY MUST NOT HAVE MADE IT.

35:00.663 --> 35:03.101
-WE HAVE TO SEE. HANS,
CAN YOU COME HELP ME?

35:03.231 --> 35:05.015
THERE'S SOMETHING
BLOCKING THE DOOR.

35:13.981 --> 35:15.287
-HANS: IT'S BLOCKED.

35:17.767 --> 35:20.857
-I GOTTA GET THROUGH
THERE. HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

35:35.045 --> 35:37.396
THEY'RE BOTH DEAD AND
IT'S COMPLETELY COLLAPSED.

35:46.013 --> 35:49.103
-WE'RE ALL GOING
TO DIE. NO ONE KNOW.

35:52.150 --> 35:53.325
-THERE'S GOT TO
BE A WAY OUT.

35:55.240 --> 35:59.244
-WE CAN'T USE THE EMERGENCY
DOOR. IT ALL GOT CRUSHED.

36:03.030 --> 36:04.249
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

36:07.469 --> 36:10.037
-THE WHOLE GALLEY'S CAVED
IN, WE CAN'T GET OUT THIS WAY.

36:10.690 --> 36:13.562
-IT'S RAN. WE'RE
ALL GONNA DIE.

36:16.957 --> 36:19.133
WE'RE ALL GONNA DIE.
I DON'T WANNA DIE.

36:23.181 --> 36:27.141
-[SHOUTING]

36:49.468 --> 36:51.165
-CODY, WHAT'S WRONG?

36:51.296 --> 36:53.733
-MY RIBS, FEELS LIKE
I BROKE A COUPLE.

36:53.863 --> 36:54.777
I'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

36:56.518 --> 36:58.303
-CODY, THE FRONT OF
THE PLANE IS GONE.

36:59.129 --> 37:00.740
-APRIL, I GOTTA FIND HER.

37:00.870 --> 37:03.351
-CODY, IT'S GONE.
FIRST CLASS BROKE OFF.

37:04.483 --> 37:06.746
IT EITHER SANK OR IT WAS
DESTROYED IN THE IMPACT.

37:06.876 --> 37:08.965
-NO, THERE'S NO WAY.

37:32.337 --> 37:33.642
-SHARK!

37:33.773 --> 37:38.865
-[SCREAMING AND SHOUTING]

38:23.257 --> 38:25.781
-APRIL: IS THERE A
FLASHLIGHT ON BOARD?

38:26.434 --> 38:28.306
-IT SHOULD BE RIGHT
OVER THERE SOME WHERE.

38:33.746 --> 38:36.270
-OH, GOD. OH, MY GOD.

38:36.401 --> 38:37.271
-WHAT'S WRONG?

38:37.880 --> 38:39.012
-I'M HAVING A CONTRACTION.

38:40.405 --> 38:42.189
-SHE'S GOING TO
HAVE A BABY.

38:42.320 --> 38:43.408
-APRIL: NO, SHE'S NOT.

38:43.538 --> 38:45.584
-YES, I AM.

38:45.714 --> 38:46.933
-JUST HANG IN
THERE, FRANCINE.

38:47.063 --> 38:48.151
-APRIL: GOT IT.

38:51.198 --> 38:52.721
-I'M HAVING ANOTHER ONE.

38:52.852 --> 38:55.637
-OKAY, TAKE A DEEP
BREATH. HOLD IT, HOLD IT.

38:55.768 --> 38:56.725
LET IT OUT.

38:56.856 --> 38:58.858
TAKE ANOTHER DEEP BREATH.

39:00.686 --> 39:03.210
-COME ON. GIVE ME YOUR
HAND, GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

39:03.341 --> 39:05.125
-GRAB ON, PAL. GRAB ON.

39:12.219 --> 39:13.351
-YOU GUYS ALL RIGHT?

39:29.367 --> 39:32.935
-OH, MY GOD. OH, MY GOD.

39:33.066 --> 39:39.028
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

40:18.372 --> 40:23.464
-[END THEME PLAYING]
